Class TigerHelpers.PoseEstimate

java.lang.Object
com.titaniumtigers4829.TigerHelpers.PoseEstimate
Enclosing class:
TigerHelpers
public static class TigerHelpers.PoseEstimate extends Object
Represents a Limelight pose estimate from Limelight's NetworkTables output. This is for any botpose estimate, so MegaTag1 or MegaTag2

      Initializes a PoseEstimate object with the provided data.
      Parameters:
      pose - The estimated 2D pose of the robot, including position and rotation.
      timestampSeconds - The timestamp of the pose estimate in seconds since the Limelight booted up.
      latency - The latency of the pose estimate in milliseconds.
      tagCount - The number of april tags used to calculate the pose estimate.
      tagSpan - The max distance, in meters, between april tags used to calculate the pose estimate.
      avgTagDist - The average distance, in meters, between the Limelight and the april tags used to calculate the pose estimate.
      avgTagArea - The average area, in square meters, of april tags used to calculate the pose estimate.
      rawFiducials - An array of RawFiducial used to calculate the pose estimate.
      isMegaTag2 - true if the pose estimate is calculated using MegaTag2, false if using MegaTag1.
